ascii table: define number values that will correspond to character (letters, symbols , numbers)

			910: 57+49+48 = 154
			9: 57
			1: 49
			0: 48

	byte' range: 127


data: a piece of information

database: collection of data
		human brain
		Book

		improves the availibity of info

info: availability

file: used for storing the data

sublime: text editor

different types of files:

		file names:                   extension:
		text file                        .txt
		word                             .doc
		PDF                              .pdf
		picture                          .png, .jpg

		Java                             .java
		HTML						     .html
		feature                          .feature
		properties                       .properties

		EVERY SINGLE FILE HAS IT'S OWN UNIQUE EXTENSION


Folder: stores the files in an organized manned
	creating folder:
			Mac:
				right click -> new folder

			Windows:
				right clcik -> select new -> folder


path: address of the file or folder


power shell and terminal: used for giving command to the computer
	Mac:
		terminal: click the search -> type "Terminal" -> hit "Enter"

	Windows:
		powershell: click the search box-> type "powershell" -> hit "Enter"

		to run powershell as admin:
				click the search box-> type "powershell" ->  right click -> click "run as administrator"


FOR WINDOWS ONLY:
	to find path: hold shift button -> right click the folder/file - > copy as path


shortcuts:
	Mac:
		copy: Command + C
		paste: Command + V
		undo: Command + Z

		save: Command + S
		delete: Command + delete (moves to trash can)
		delete permanently:  command + Option + Delete

	Windows:
		copy: Control + C
		paste: Control + V
		undo: Control + Z

		save: Control + s
		delete: delete  (moves to trash can)
		delete permanently: shift + delete


command: giving order to computer

basic commands:
	pwd: print working directory
	ls: lists all the files and folders in the directory
	cd: change directory
		(if the directory name contains space(s), directory name MUST be given in double quote)
	cd ..:goes to previous directory
	clear: clears the terminal
	mkdir: creating directory

	md (for windows only): creating directory
			md foldername1, foldername2

	rm -r: removes the item


